                <head>No. 303.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Morgan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-04-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 12, 1886</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Bayard informs Mr. Morgan that his instruction No. 148, of March 20, 1886,
                    was intended for communication to the Mexican Government as reciting facts which
                    might aid it in the investigation which it had undertaken as to the killing of
                    Captain Crawford at Teopar, and as showing the necessity of punishing those who
                    were guilty of his death and of rendering such occurrences impossible
                    hereafter.</p>
            </div>
